# Preview

Rush's previewable surface is the static documentation site in `website/`.
There is no package-manager dev server, login, database, or seed data.

Run this from the repository root as a normal foreground shell command:

```sh
python3 -m http.server 4173 --bind 0.0.0.0 --directory website
```

Wait until this succeeds:

```sh
curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:4173/ >/dev/null
```

Then make sure the Preview tab has a link for the docs preview. For a local
non-orb session, write `.amp/previews/rush-docs.json` with:

```json
{
  "links": [
    { "label": "Rush docs", "url": "http://localhost:4173/" }
  ]
}
```

If running inside an orb, do not share raw `localhost` or `127.0.0.1` URLs with
the user. Use whatever preview URL mechanism is configured for the orb, validate
the external URL with `curl -fsS`, and write that URL to
`.amp/previews/rush-docs.json` instead. Tailscale is one supported option, but
not a requirement. If no orb preview mechanism is configured, say so instead of
guessing a URL.
